<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <nav class="sidebar">
            <h1>Poet's Palette</h1>
            <p>
                <strong>Poem's Palette</strong> is a creative project utilizing the power of GPT-3.5 Turbo to generate personalized poetry. 
                Using the latest advancements in AI, you can provide a title, specify the emotion you want the poem to convey, 
                the tone in which it should be presented, and add context to shape the theme or background of the poem.
            </p>
            <p>
                GPT-3.5 Turbo is part of OpenAI's models designed to understand natural language and generate human-like text. 
                It is ideal for tasks such as text generation, creative writing, and more. 
                In this app, you will witness its ability to craft beautiful poems that evoke specific feelings and themes, 
                showing how AI can contribute to the art of storytelling and poetry creation.
            </p>
        </nav>
        
        <main class="content">
            <h1>Emotion-driven Poem Generation using GPT-3.5 Turbo</h1>
            
            <% if (error) { %>
                <div class="alert error">
                    <%= error %>
                </div>
            <% } %>
            
            <form action="/generate" method="POST">
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="title">Enter the title of the poem:</label>
                    <input type="text" id="title" name="title" value="<%= locals.formData ? formData.title : '' %>" required>
                </div>
                
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="emotion">Enter the emotion you want the poem to convey:</label>
                    <input type="text" id="emotion" name="emotion" value="<%= locals.formData ? formData.emotion : '' %>" required>
                </div>
                
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="tone">Enter the tone in which the poem should be written:</label>
                    <input type="text" id="tone" name="tone" value="<%= locals.formData ? formData.tone : '' %>" required>
                </div>
                
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="context">Enter the context or theme for the poem:</label>
                    <textarea id="context" name="context" rows="4" required><%= locals.formData ? formData.context : '' %></textarea>
                </div>
                
                <button type="submit" class="btn">Generate Poem</button>
            </form>
            
            <% if (poem) { %>
                <div class="poem-container">
                    <h2>Generated Poem</h2>
                    <div class="poem">
                        <%= poem.replace(/\n/g, '<br>') %>
                    </div>
                </div>
            <% } %>
        </main>
    </div>
    
    <script src="/js/script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
